sql:
SELECT bam_service_id, AVG(bam_avg_res_time) AS avg_response_time
FROM bam_data
GROUP BY bam_service_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Sailed beyond the horizon of their performance expectations" metaphorically refers to services whose performance (average response time) exceeds the acceptable limit (threshold value).;
- "Set benchmarks" refers to the predefined threshold values for response times.;
- The time period of a year is considered from months 1 to 12.;
- The services and their corresponding average response times are listed.

sql:
SELECT bam_avg_res_time
FROM bam_data
WHERE bam_service_id = 1 AND bam_month_id = 202310;

external_knowledge:
- "basking in the glow of speed" metaphorically refers to services with shorter average response times; 
- "struggling in the shadow of slowness" metaphorically refers to services with longer average response times; 
- "the month where we currently stand" refers to the current month based on the system's current timestamp.

sql:
SELECT AVG(bam_avg_res_time) 
FROM bam_data 
WHERE bam_avg_res_time > (SELECT AVG(bam_avg_res_time) FROM bam_data WHERE bam_avg_res_time > 0);

SELECT service_name
FROM bam_services
